# Integration Test Credentials
# ============================
# The RECOMMENDED way to set up credentials is to run start-dev.sh first:
#
#   export AWS_PROFILE=your-profile && ./start-dev.sh
#
# This generates app/orchestrator-agent/.env with real credentials fetched
# from AWS SSM. The integration tests automatically load that file.
#
# Alternatively, copy this file to .env.integration and fill in values below.
# .env.integration takes priority over the orchestrator .env file.
# .env.integration is gitignored and will NOT be committed.
#
# Only fill in the providers you want to test. Tests for providers
# without credentials will be automatically skipped.
#
# Run: cd app/orchestrator-agent && uv run pytest tests/integration/ -m integration -v --timeout=120

# --- AWS Bedrock (Claude models) ---
# Option A: Explicit credentials (e.g., from aws sso export)
# AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=AKIA...
# AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=...
# AWS_SESSION_TOKEN=...
# AWS_BEDROCK_REGION=us-east-1

# Option B: Leave these commented out to use default credential chain
# (reads from ~/.aws/credentials, ~/.aws/config, or aws sso login)
# Just set the region:
# AWS_BEDROCK_REGION=us-east-1

# --- Azure OpenAI (GPT models) ---
# AZURE_OPENAI_ENDPOINT=https://your-resource.openai.azure.com
# AZURE_OPENAI_API_KEY=your-api-key

# --- Google Vertex AI (Gemini models) ---
# GCP_KEY={"type":"service_account", ...}
# GCP_PROJECT_ID=your-project-id
# GCP_LOCATION=europe-west4
